&lt;div class=&#34;lightbox&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle2&#34;&gt;
      
      &lt;img src=&#34;http://dev.bluevisual.tv/images/work/vapetraze-02.jpg&#34;&gt;
      
    &lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;project-image&#34;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34;&gt;
    
    &lt;img src=&#34;http://dev.bluevisual.tv/images/work/vapetraze-01.jpg&#34;&gt;
    
  &lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;input type=&#34;checkbox&#34; name=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34; id=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;lightbox&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34;&gt;
      
      &lt;img src=&#34;http://dev.bluevisual.tv/images/work/vapetraze-01.jpg&#34;&gt;
      
    &lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

Luckily in one of my personal projects, I made a procedural circuit generator, which sped up a lot of the asset creation time. I was able to randomize and generate circuits over and over with ease until I got just the one I wanted.
&lt;div class=&#34;project-image&#34;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle3&#34;&gt;
    
    &lt;img src=&#34;http://dev.bluevisual.tv/images/work/vapetraze-03.jpg&#34;&gt;
    
  &lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
